3. Custom Scripts & Configurations

PH4NTXM’s custom scripts, system tweaks, and configurations developed by the PH4NTXM team are released under the GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3).

You are free to copy, modify, and redistribute them under the same license.

All derivative work must retain GPLv3 licensing.


4. Upstream Software

PH4NTXM GNU/Linux includes software packages provided by Debian and other upstream projects.

PH4NTXM does not modify upstream source code beyond build configuration and packaging unless explicitly stated.

Each package is distributed under its original license (GPL, LGPL, MIT, BSD, or other open-source licenses).

Users must comply with the license terms of individual software packages.


